        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 1:17PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 116 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sturdivants, or 12 miles southeast of Monroe, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wadesboro, Ansonville, Polkton, Lilesville, Morven, Peachland,
McFarlan, Blewett Falls Lake, and White Store.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.</instruction>
